    "Additionally, it is worth noting that the dilated neighborhood graph is computed on the face coordinates in the metric space and therefore remains static.",
    "Consequently, it can be precomputed, thereby saving computational resources.This operation is integrated in the network as a middle layer after the local edge convolution and operates on the features extracted from the preceding layers.",
    "ExperimentIn this section, we provide a brief description of the competing methods that we used for comparison against our own approach.",
    "Additionally, we outline the experimental setup.",
    "Competing MethodsTo demonstrate the efficacy of our proposed method, we compared it with three state-of-the-art techniques in 3D surface segmentation (PointNet++ [16], PointNext [18] and DGCNN [18]), as well as two state-of-the-art techniques specifically designed for 3D dental model segmentation (MeshSegNet [21] and TSGCNet [8])."
